RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 11300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: BARRELHOUSE stalked the early pace two deep, moved to even terms at the seven eighths pole and took the nod past the nine sixteenths, dueled clear approaching the three eighths, contested the advantage nearest the rail on the far turn and dug in determinedly to edge out the game stretch challenge of MARCUS JUNIUS, who settled in the three path, gave chase passing the half mile pole, moved to even terms two deep midway on the far turn and dug in gamely to the finish. ONLY GET'N BETTER raced well off the pace in the five path the first turn then moved to the inside, bid leaving the three eighths pole and steadily improved from that point, rounded the far turn about the five path and came along for third later yards. S S SPARTAN ENERGY raced in the three path the opening turn then saved some ground, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path then flattened in the lane. LEG UP set the early pace inside but was met at even terms leaving the seven eighths pole, gave up the nod at the nine sixteenths, chased from the half mile pole but dropped back toward the three eighths and faded at the rail on the far turn. TYRY TYRANNOSAURUS rounded the opening turn about the four path and showed little response through the backstretch. CALIFORNIA GHOST rated close to the early pace inside but faded at the rail on the second turn. I SEE NOTHING saved ground off the early pace, eased out into the backstretch but showed little response.
